mindmap
  root((Human Dietary Protein Digestion))
    Ingestion & Stomach
      Chewing & swallowing
      Gastric acid (HCl) pH ~1.5–2
      Pepsinogen → pepsin
      Pepsin: endopeptidase
      Large polypeptides formed
    Small Intestine — Pancreas
      Enterokinase activates trypsinogen
      Trypsin, chymotrypsin, elastase
      Carboxypeptidases (exopeptidases)
      Oligopeptides + free AAs
    Brush Border
      Dipeptidyl peptidase IV
      Aminopeptidases
      Dipeptides & tripeptides
      PEPT1 transporter
      Sodium-dependent AA transporters
    Absorption & Fate
      Jejunum: primary site
      Portal vein → liver
      First-pass metabolism
      Systemic aminoacidemia
    Protein Source Speed
      Whey: fast (~1–2 h peak)
      Casein: slow (curd, 7–8 h)
      Plant: variable, often slower
      Matrix & antinutrients matter
